, new connections between Asia and Latin America revive the \"swarmlike buzz of activity\" around and across the perimeter of the Pacific that Claude Lévi-Strauss had pitted against \"the great Atlantic silence\" prior to the European \"discovery\" of the Americas. This course explores different perspectives on the intercultural study of Asia and Latin America with the aim of rethinking the Transpacific as a method and a lens for comparison that challenges conventional geopolitical models, rather than simply an area or a region. To do so, we will explore multiple meanings, methodologies, and mappings of the Transpacific through a wide range of real and imagined links between Asian and Latin American literature, art, and theory: from diaspora, textual circulation, and cultural exchanges to uneven dialogues, compelling analogies, and conceptual affinities.","catalogBreadth":"(GB)","catalogDistr":"(LA-AS)","catalogLang":"","catalogForbiddenOverlaps":"","catalogWhenOffered":"Spring.","catalogComments":"Co-meets with COML 6706/PORT 6540.","catalogPrereqCoreq":"","catalogFee":"","catalogSatisfiesReq":"","catalogPermission":"","catalogCourseSubfield":"","catalogOutcomes":null,"acadCareer":"UG","acadGroup":"AS"},{"strm":2587,"crseId":359091,"crseOfferNbr":1,"subject":"PORT","catalogNbr":"6400","titleShort":"Special Topics Brazilian Lit","titleLong":"Special Topics in Brazilian Literature","enrollGroups":[{"classSections":[{"ssrComponent":"IND","ssrComponentLong":"Independent Study","section":"601","classNbr":15789,"meetings":[{"classMtgNbr":1,"timeStart":"","timeEnd":"","startDt":"01/21/2015","endDt":"05/06/2015","instructors":[{"instrAssignSeq":1,"netid":"pre5","firstName":"Pedro","middleName":"Rabelo","lastName":"Erber"}],"pattern":"","facilityDescr":null,"bldgDescr":null,"facilityDescrshort":null,"meetingTopicDescription":""}],"notes":[],"campus":"MAIN","campusDescr":"Ithaca","location":"ITH","locationDescr":"Ithaca, NY (Main Campus)","startDt":"01/21/2015","endDt":"05/0